Subject: [PATCH 70/98] arm64: dts: qcom: sc8280xp: Describe TCSR download mode
 register

To allow for swift EDL reboots, describe the respective register under
the scm node.

Signed-off-by: Konrad Dybcio <konrad.dybcio@linaro.org>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20240307-topic-8280_nodes-v1-4-4eba20e08902@linaro.org
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sc8280xp.dtsi | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sc8280xp.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sc8280xp.dtsi
index 6e0daa959ed..cc69ee1d612 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sc8280xp.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sc8280xp.dtsi
@@ -301,6 +301,7 @@ firmware {
 		scm: scm {
 			compatible = "qcom,scm-sc8280xp", "qcom,scm";
 			interconnects = <&aggre2_noc MASTER_CRYPTO 0 &mc_virt SLAVE_EBI1 0>;
+			qcom,dload-mode = <&tcsr 0x13000>;
 		};
 	};
 
